29328.name: Credit
29328.desc: This currency, used by the Interastral Peace Corporation to settle accounts with its customers, is now widely accepted as the hard currency for space travel.
29328.lore: "People run around fighting and trading for numbers in a terminal, but the truly precious cannot be bought."

125435.name: Tracks of Destiny
125435.lore: Your victory is secured by countless failures, and the small steps you have taken led you to the turning point of fate.

267807.name: A Glass of the Besotted Era
267807.desc: A golden goblet of fine wine held by the troupe's cupbearer. Can be used for the Ascension of Wind characters.
267807.lore:
A group of believers treads across countless stars, seeking memories of numerous fine wines, brewing their offerings in dreams. Another group of believers turns themselves into yeast, fermenting ancient faiths sealed by the dust of time, distilling their ideals within dreams.

"At this moment, a cup of nectar blends with a goblet of poison, intoxicating this era together and poisoning the future with the past."

409960.name: Traveler's Guide
409960.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>20,000</nobr> Character EXP.
409960.lore:
Required reading for world exploration. Press the "Read" button to tune in to an attractive voice in a language you understand, telling you about the legendary encounters of renowned adventurers across different worlds as well as the precious wisdom and knowledge that they have gathered.

"All-new series of the Traveler's Guide, The Chef's Manual to Galactic Cuisine, is now available for purchase."
"For submissions, please connect to synesthesia beacon ERD-23θ to contact an Intelligentsia Guild representative. Method of payment can be arranged to your convenience."

409961.name: Adventure Log
409961.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>5000</nobr> Character EXP.
409961.lore:
A neatly organized collection of educational adventure notes containing countless illustrations and texts entailing adventures from beginning to end, as well as valuable information and survival-related techniques.

"Why not just digitize it and save it on a photolith disk? That'd be much more convenient."
"Advanced technology is far more fragile than you'd think when faced with stellar storms and neuron flow eruptions. Besides, I'm sure the author of this book wanted people to read it in the simplest of ways."

409962.name: Travel Encounters
409962.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>1000</nobr> Character EXP.
409962.lore:
A travel diary with messy handwriting and random content. It's not of much use to you.

"Dan Heng, hurry up and finish reading it so you can throw it away."

549437.name: Thief's Instinct
549437.desc: A small amount of anti-matter. Crude material used for enhancement.
549437.lore:
A small amount of anti-matter that emanates out of the Voidranger: Reaver like the materialization of its destructive instinct.

"They are all looking forward to the moment of obliteration, when they will be reforged and fused with the entire world."
comeFrom: Dropped by enemies in Divergent Universe

633378.name: Usurper's Scheme
633378.desc: A moderate amount of anti-matter. Normal material used for enhancement.
633378.lore:
A moderate amount of anti-matter that floats around the Voidranger: Distorter. The amount of matter and anti-matter particles has reached a dangerous balance...

"They are all looking forward to the moment of obliteration, when they will be reforged and fused with the entire world."
comeFrom: Antimatter Legion at Equilibrium Level 2 or higher
Dropped by enemies in Divergent Universe

635680.name: Borisin Teeth
635680.desc: Broken teeth fragments left behind during the borisin conquests. Used to level up Traces slightly for Destruction characters.
635680.lore:
Borisin consider their teeth as a warrior's blade and weapon.
The borisin worship warriors possessing supreme power. In their tribes, where the strong rule the weak, those with dental caries will only be discarded by the group.

"O, Brood Lord, grant us sharp teeth and claws."

717319.name: Conqueror's Will
717319.desc: Condensed anti-matter. Advanced material used for enhancement.
717319.lore:
Highly condensed anti-matter within the body of the Voidranger: Trampler. The moment of obliteration is the trumpet call for civilizations' destruction.

"They are all looking forward to the moment of obliteration, when they will be reforged and fused with the entire world."
comeFrom: Antimatter Legion at Equilibrium Level 4 or higher
Dropped by enemies in Divergent Universe

836266.name: Moon Rage Fang
836266.desc: Terrifying tusks left behind during the borisin conquests. Used to level up Traces significantly for Destruction characters.
836266.lore:
Borisin can further enhance their bodies through their innate "Moon Rage."
The battle-frenzied warriors exhibit incredible healing abilities, shedding the blood of their enemies in a sanguine mist together with the unbridled growth of their muscles and bones.

"O, Brood Lord, grant us divine strength."

920207.name: Lupitoxin Sawteeth
920207.desc: Blood-sucking sharp fangs left behind during the borisin conquests. Used to level up Traces moderately for Destruction characters.
920207.lore:
Borisin consider their teeth as a warrior's blade and weapon.
A maddening impulse flows through the borisin blood. Fueled by Lupitoxin, they rend their enemies with their sawteeth and suck their blood, and are undefeated.

"O, Brood Lord, grant us steel skin and bones."

985668.name: Destroyer's Final Road
985668.lore:
The Leviathan's heart has stopped beating, but its mind lives on despite being trapped in a case. As long as the lid is closed, its mind is simultaneously both alive and dead, driving the engine of destruction.

"Doomsday Beast, a blight made in the Warforge using what's left of a Leviathan and the weeping bones of thousands of the dead. It longs for the destruction of the universe and itself."

ranks.name: The Lost White Walls
ranks.descHash: Increases the Ultimate DMG dealt by <nobr>Saber</nobr> by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>. After <nobr>Saber</nobr> uses Basic ATK or Skill, gains <nobr>#2[i]</nobr> "Core Resonance."

ranks.name: The Lost Oath of the Round Table
ranks.descHash: For every 1 point of "Core Resonance" gained in this battle, <nobr>Saber</nobr>'s DMG dealt ignores <nobr>#2[f1]%</nobr> of the target's DEF. This effect stacks up to <nobr>#3[i]</nobr> time(s). When triggering the "Core Resonance" effect to boost Skill's multiplier, each point of "Core Resonance" additionally increases the DMG multiplier for the current instance of Skill by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>.

ranks.name: A Wish Across Fifteen Centuries
ranks.descHash:
Ultimate Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Basic ATK Lv. +1, up to a maximum of Lv. 10.

ranks.name: The Saga of Sixteen Winter Days
ranks.descHash: Increases <nobr>Saber's</nobr> Wind <u>RES PEN</u> by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>. After using Ultimate, increases <nobr>Saber's</nobr> Wind <u>RES PEN</u> by <nobr>#2[i]%</nobr>. This effect stacks up to <nobr>#3[i]</nobr> time(s).

ranks.name: The Dreamed Utopian Dawn
ranks.descHash:
Skill Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Talent Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.

ranks.name: The Long Fated Night
ranks.descHash: The Wind <u>RES PEN</u> of the Ultimate DMG dealt by <nobr>Saber</nobr> increases by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>. The amount of overflow Energy that can be accumulated with the Trace "Blessing of the Lake" increases to <nobr>#4[i]</nobr>. After using Ultimate for the first time upon entering combat, regenerates a fixed amount of <nobr>#3[i]</nobr> Energy for <nobr>Saber</nobr>. This effect can trigger 1 time after every <nobr>#2[i]</nobr> Ultimate use(s).

skills.descHash: Deals Wind DMG equal to #1[i]% of Saber's ATK to one designated enemy.
skills.name: Invisible Air: Barrier of the Wind King

skills.descHash: Deals Wind DMG equal to #1[i]% of Saber's ATK to one designated enemy, and deals Wind DMG equal to #2[i]% of Saber's ATK to adjacent targets. If Saber currently holds "Core Resonance" and her Energy can be fully regenerated by consuming "Core Resonance" after this instance of Skill attack, then increases the multiplier for this instance of Skill. For every 1 point of "Core Resonance," increases the DMG multiplier for this instance of Skill by #4[f1]%. And after the attack, consumes all "Core Resonance" to regenerate Energy for Saber. Otherwise, immediately gains #3[i] point(s) of "Core Resonance."
skills.name: Strike Air: Hammer of the Wind King

skills.descHash: Deals Wind DMG equal to #1[i]% of Saber's ATK to all enemies, and additionally deals #3[i] instance(s) of DMG, with each instance being Wind DMG equal to #2[i]% of Saber's ATK dealt to one random enemy. After using Ultimate, the next Basic ATK switches to "Release, the Golden Scepter," and only "Release, the Golden Scepter" can be used.
skills.name: Excalibur

skills.descHash: When entering combat, gains #8[i] "Core Resonance" point(s). When any ally target uses Ultimate, increases the DMG dealt by Saber by #3[i]% for #4[i] turn(s) and gains #1[i] "Core Resonance" point(s). For every 1 "Core Resonance" point consumed, regenerates a fixed amount of #5[f1] Energy for Saber.
skills.name: Dragon Reactor Core

skills.descHash: Attacks an enemy, and when the battle starts, reduces their Toughness of the corresponding Type.
skills.name: Attack

skills.descHash: After using Technique, at the start of the next battle, increases <nobr>Saber's</nobr> ATK by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> for <nobr>#2[i]</nobr> turn(s) and gains <nobr>#3[i]</nobr> "Core Resonance."
skills.name: Behold, the King of Knights

skills.descHash: Gains #2[i] point(s) of "Core Resonance" and deals Wind DMG to all enemies equal to #1[i]% of Saber's ATK. When this ability is used, if the number of enemy targets is 2 or 1, additionally deals Wind DMG to all enemies equal to #3[i]% or #4[i]% of Saber's ATK respectively.
skills.name: Release, the Golden Scepter

embedBonusSkill.descHash: Increases <nobr>Saber's</nobr> CRIT Rate by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>. When entering combat or when using her Enhanced Basic ATK, gains the "Mana Burst" effect. Under this effect, if <nobr>Saber</nobr> has "Core Resonance" and her Energy can be fully regenerated by using her Skill and consuming "Core Resonance," then consumes "Mana Burst" to recover 1 Skill Point for allies, and causes <nobr>Saber</nobr> to immediately take action.
embedBonusSkill.name: Knight of the Dragon

embedBonusSkill.descHash: <nobr>Saber</nobr> can accumulate up to <nobr>#1[i]</nobr> overflow Energy. After using Ultimate, the overflow Energy is cleared and a corresponding amount of Energy is regenerated. When the battle starts, if Energy is below <nobr>#3[i]%</nobr>, it is regenerated to <nobr>#2[i]%</nobr>.
embedBonusSkill.name: Blessing of the Lake

embedBonusSkill.descHash: When using Skill, increases <nobr>Saber's</nobr> CRIT DMG by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> for <nobr>#2[i]</nobr> turns. During this battle, for every 1 point of "Core Resonance" gained, increases <nobr>Saber's</nobr> CRIT DMG by <nobr>#3[i]%</nobr>, stacking up to <nobr>#4[i]</nobr> time(s).
embedBonusSkill.name: Crown of the Star
